  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b95\u0bcb\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0baa\u0bbe\u0baf \u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b9c\u0baa\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bb5\u0bc8 \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bb5\u0bc7\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd - 17 \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bbf\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc2\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bae\u0bbe \u0b85\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0ba3\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b95\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Gotabaya Rajapaksa should be investigated - 17 organizations write to Singapore Attorney General's Department",
      "author": "Rajeeban",
      "body_lines": [
        "17 organizations, including the International Human Rights Watch, have jointly requested Singapore to prosecute former President Gotabaya Rajapaksa.",
        "In a letter written to the Solicitor General of the International Affairs Division of the Attorney General's Department of Singapore, the 17 organizations requested that the former President of Sri Lanka be investigated.",
        "17 organizations have said that we, the undersigned organizations, immediately request Gotabaya Rajapaksa to investigate the serious crimes committed in Sri Lanka under international laws and file a case if appropriate.",
        "On July 14, Gotabaya Rajapaksa submitted his resignation from Singapore via e-mail due to which 17 organizations have informed him that he is not entitled to leave.",
        "In 2008-2009, when Gotabaya Rajapaksa served as Defense Secretary, the Sri Lankan government launched a human rights abuse military operation in the north-eastern regions of Sri Lanka, which was under the control of the LTTE.",
        "The Sri Lankan government ordered Tamil civilians into safe zones and then attacked hospitals and makeshift hospitals more than 30 times, killing an estimated 70,000 to 169,796 civilians in the final moments of Sri Lanka's war.",
        "Rajapaksa should be investigated for possible responsibility based on command responsibility, and there are public reports that Gotabaya Rajapaksa ordered the killing of LTTE members and their families when they surrendered.",
        "Gotabaya Rajapaksa directed the planned widespread bombing of hospitals, repeatedly stating that civilians were targets and civilians were legitimate targets.",
        "Singapore should conduct investigations for serious international crimes committed in Sri Lanka and apply appropriate justice against Rajapaksa.",
        "The Attorney General may initiate investigations against Gotabaya for gross injustices under international law and applicable domestic law.",
        "Rajapaksa has been credibly accused of committing the gravest crimes in the world, and Singapore should not give asylum to a person associated with massive abuses, but rather Singapore should fulfill its international justice obligations and immediately put Rajapaksa to trial for the crimes mentioned above, 17 organizations said."
      ],
